The model used in the IsingFit R-package39 is a binary equivalent of the Gaussian approximation method. Its variables can have only two states and interactions are considered pairwise. The aforementioned model contains two node-specific parameters: the interaction parameter βjk, representing the strength of the interaction between variable j and k, and the node parameter τj, which represents the autonomous disposition of the variable to take the value of one - “1” - regardless of neighboring variables. The IsingFit model estimates the aforementioned parameters using logistic regression. Through repetition, every variable is regressed on all of the other variables. To obtain sparsity, an \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
