				\begin{document}$${\ell }_{1}$$\end{document}ℓ1-penalty is imposed on the regression coefficients. The level of shrinkage depends on the penalty parameter of the lasso. In the IsingFit method, the Extended Bayesian Information Criterion (EBIC) is used to select the set of neighbor nodes that yield the lowest EBIC and in this way constructs the final “true” network.

